message.raw:
- Rewrite XML.iterfind for more thorough support of XPath.
- Add _default_iter_path attribute for parsers like TandemXML and custom classes that have predicates in default iteration.
- TaskMappingMixin: use separate done Event for each process.
- TaskMappingMixin: raise error in map() if index is not present.
- IndexedXML: make sure _offset_index is None if use_index is False.
- XML, IndexedXML: Keep _use_index, _read_schema and _iterative as class attributes for ease of subclassing.

message.raw:
fix: Adjust how WritableIndex.load creates new instances

The current implementation of WritableIndex.load assumed that
OffsetIndex and HierarchicalOffsetIndex took two parameters,
when in reality they took only one. This lead to an error that
signaled the caller automatically rebuilding the index every time,
never benefiting from the saved index.

This change corrects the way the container is created.

message.raw:
feature:Make the charge parser used by MGFBase overrideable by inheritance

The default charge parser was written to defend against poorly formatted,
ambiguous charge states from the bad old days of low resolution instruments.
However, regexes are slow compared to exact string operations, and when the
you don't need to handle the ambiguity it can be the slowest part of parsing.
This patch allows you to override the charge parser function through inheritance
rather than by monkeypatching `pyteomics.mgf.aux._parse_charge` globally.

The new tests for the index saving process for MGF broke on Windows because of
newline conversion (\n -> \n\r), resulting in incorrect offsets. Opening the files
in binary mode ensures that the original line endings are preserved. The types of
the reference offsets' containers needed to be adjusted to satisfy Py3.6 where lists
do not equal tuples even if their contents are the same?

Lastly, PyteomicsError was defined to take only one argument, the error message
but pylint observed it was called with an additional parameter occaisionally. While
the error would result from invalid user code rather than library code, allowing it
to take additional arguments satisfied the static code checker.

feature:Make the charge parser used by MGFBase overrideable by inheritance

The default charge parser was written to defend against poorly formatted,
ambiguous charge states from the bad old days of low resolution instruments.
However, regexes are slow compared to exact string operations, and when the
you don't need to handle the ambiguity it can be the slowest part of parsing.
This patch allows you to override the charge parser function through inheritance
rather than by monkeypatching `pyteomics.mgf.aux._parse_charge` globally.

The new tests for the index saving process for MGF broke on Windows because of
newline conversion (\n -> \n\r), resulting in incorrect offsets. Opening the files
